title: Fannie Mae

creator: Fannie Mae
descriptionHtml:
Resources for homeowners and renters. Understand options for mortgage assistance and renter protections to help you stay in your home.
• Learn about forbearance and repayment options to give you breathing room during times of financial stress.
• Use our lookup tools to learn more about your home loan or rental building.
• Schedule a call with a housing counselor to discuss solutions tailored for your situation.
• Access tips for talking to your mortgage servicer or landlord.
• Quickly find help if your house or apartment has been impacted by a disaster such as a wildfire, hurricane or flood.
• Learn how to avoid foreclosure and stay in your home.
• If looking to leave your home, discover options to leave including short sale and mortgage release (deed-in-lieu of foreclosure).
descriptionShort: Learn about mortgage assistance and renter protections to stay in your home.

title: Fannie Mae

creator: Fannie Mae
descriptionHtml:
Whether you’re looking to buy a house or need options to stay in your current home – we’re here to help.
* Access the complete guide to homebuying including facts about down payment, credit score, closing costs, mortgage insurance, and making an offer.
* Use calculators to estimate what you can afford and how much you need to save.
* Save your progress as you learn the 7 steps to purchase a home.
* Quickly find help if your house or apartment has been impacted by a natural disaster such as a  wildfire, hurricane or flood.
* Learn about forbearance and repayment options to give you breathing room during times of financial stress.
* Use our lookup tools to learn more about your home loan or rental building.
* Schedule a counseling call with a housing expert to discuss solutions tailored for your situation.
descriptionShort: On-the-go resources for homebuyers, homeowners and renters.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: Introducing the complete guide to homebuying! Now you can learn all about the seven basic steps of buying a home and track your progress as you go. This update also contains calculators and tools, so you can estimate how much you can afford and what you need to save. And if you’re a renter or homeowner facing financial hardship, we still have resources to help you navigate your options.

appDetails.recentChangesHtml: This update features new homeowner projects to help you learn the basics of maintaining and protecting your home. Simple maintenance tasks will help you learn how to take care of your home’s major systems and save on energy costs. From what to do in your first month to seasonal maintenance, you can easily filter projects based on category, skill level, and the amount of time it takes to complete. And you’ll be able to go at your own pace by choosing and saving projects to complete later.
